# CHIP v2 blackwell-sm
Full Name: NVIDIA Blackwell Streaming Multiprocessor
Description:
A textual representation of a streaming multiprocessor focused on auditable module definitions, controlled composition, and deterministic parsing.
Architecture Goals:
- Express the SM as composable modules
- Keep parsing deterministic and auditable
- Support future evolution toward richer validation
Modules:
Define module Warp Scheduler:
Summary: Issues work to active warps.
Operations: select, issue, stall
Inputs: warp state, ready mask
Outputs: selected warp, issue decision
Define module Tensor Core:
Summary: Executes matrix-oriented tensor operations.
Operations: mma, accumulate, convert
Inputs: operand a, operand b, accumulator
Outputs: result fragment
Define module Register File:
Summary: Stores per-thread register state.
Operations: read, write, allocate
Inputs: thread id, register index, write value
Outputs: register value, allocation status
Instantiate:
Create 4 instances of Warp Scheduler
Create 8 instances of Tensor Core
Create 1 instances of Register File
Connect:
Warp Scheduler -> Tensor Core
Tensor Core -> Register File
Output: SM tile with scheduling, tensor execution, and register storage.
